# Flower Business Domain

## Inventory — FIFO (First In, First Out)
- Inventory uses FIFO for perishable goods
- Each flower batch has: arrival_date, supplier, expiry_date, quantity, unit_price
- When deducting stock, always select batches ordered by arrival_date ASC (oldest first)
- If oldest batch has insufficient quantity, take what's available and move to next batch
- Deduction must be atomic (transaction.atomic) — no partial deductions on failure
- Track deduction history: which batch, how many units, for which order

## Bouquet = Recipe (Tech Card)
- BouquetRecipe = recipe (tech card): list of components with quantities
- BouquetComponent links flower to recipe with quantity and unit
- When assembling bouquet, auto-deduct components from inventory using FIFO
- selling_price = (sum of component costs + labor_cost + packaging) × (1 + margin_percent / 100)
- Recalculate selling_price when component prices change

## Order Lifecycle
- Order statuses: new → paid → assembling → assembled → delivering → delivered → completed
- Status transitions are strict — no skipping steps
- Each status change triggers notification (customer + staff) via Celery
- Each status change logged in OrderStatusLog with timestamp, user, old_status, new_status
- Order can also be: cancelled, refunded (from any status before delivered)

## Delivery
- Delivery has time slots (e.g., 09:00-12:00, 12:00-15:00, 15:00-18:00, 18:00-21:00)
- Delivery zones with different pricing based on geography
- Courier assignment considers: zone, shift schedule, current load
- Photo confirmation required on delivery (photo_before_delivery field)

## Customer Card
- Customer identified primarily by phone number
- Track: allergies, preferred flowers, preferred color palette, memorable dates
- memorable_dates: JSON array of {date, description, reminder_days_before}
- Automatic trigger: send reminder N days before memorable date
- Segment: VIP, regular, new, churned (based on order frequency and recency)

## Expiry Alerts
- "Hot flowers" alert when expiry_date < today + 2 days
- Daily Celery task scans all batches and generates alerts
- Alert appears on dashboard and as push notification to manager

## Write-offs
- Write-offs require reason: wilted, damaged, defective, expired, other
- Write-off reduces batch quantity
- All write-offs tracked for loss analytics
- Monthly write-off report auto-generated

## Pricing Rules
- Prices can vary by delivery zone
- Holiday surcharge (configurable dates and percentages)
- Bonus program: cashback percentage on order total → added to customer bonus_balance
- Bonus can be used as partial payment (configurable max percentage)
